 Former Captain, Benin Golf Club, Kingsley Okunbor (left); Edo State Deputy Governor, Philip Shaibu; Governor Godwin Obaseki; Secretary to the State Government (SSG), Osarodion Ogie and others during the tee-off of the golf tournament at the ongoing National Sports Festival, Edo 2020, in Benin City…yesterday.  Obaseki said this when he teed-off the Edo 2020 golf tournament in Benin City, the state capital. The governor was joined by the Deputy Governor, Comrade Philip Shaibu; Secretary to the State Government, Osarodion Ogie Esq. and the representative of the President of the Nigerian Golf Federation, Thaddeus Wilmen and other golfers, in Benin City. Addressing journalists after teeing off the tournament, Obaseki said: “The purpose of the National Sports Festival is to bring men and women together in the spirit of oneness and unity so that they can have a common purpose. Our country needs healing, unity and a sense of purpose and that is why we are hosting the sports festival. “It is not necessary that we host and win. For us, we know we have all it takes but as sports men and women, we will let excellence prevail.” On the issue of sustainability of the world-class sports facilities in the state, Governor Obaseki noted: “There are tremendous changes in Edo today as regards how we maintain the structures and institutions. It has to do with the people, with capacity building and making sure you have the right processes and procedures.”  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .